// Focused schema for AI-friendly granular knowledge management
// ================================================================

Comp Artifact parent . Find
----------------------------------------------------------------
* Self-contained knowledge unit optimized for AI consumption
* Each artifact is 10-30 lines with single clear purpose
----------------------------------------------------------------
	Element name        key  .        + Unique artifact identifier
	Element category    word .        * Optional category word
	Element topic_type  word .        * Optional type word
	Element doc         text .        * Not used in definition files

Comp Link parent Artifact FindIn
----------------------------------------------------------------
* Typed relationship creating validated knowledge graph
* Only component requiring strict validation
----------------------------------------------------------------
	Element concept     ref  Artifact + Target artifact (must exist)
	Element relation    ref  Artifact + Relationship type (must exist)

Comp O parent Artifact FindIn
----------------------------------------------------------------
* Overview summary (1-3 sentences)
* Appears after Artifact and Links
----------------------------------------------------------------
	Element note        text .        * Overview content

Comp Section parent Artifact FindIn
----------------------------------------------------------------
* Optional structure for longer artifacts
* Uses level for heading hierarchy
----------------------------------------------------------------
	Element name        word .        + Section identifier
	Element level       tree .        + Heading depth (2=h2, 3=h3, 4=h4)
	Element note        text .        * Section heading text

Comp D parent Section FindIn
----------------------------------------------------------------
* Document content preserving markdown
----------------------------------------------------------------
	Element note        text .        * Content with markdown formatting

// ================================================================
// STANDARD RELATION TYPES (as regular Artifacts in definition files)
// ================================================================

// Artifact prerequisite relation
//   O Must understand this concept first
//
// Artifact related relation  
//   O Provides additional context without dependency
//
// Artifact extension relation
//   O Builds upon the linked concept
//
// Artifact example relation
//   O Concrete demonstration
//
// Artifact contrast relation
//   O Alternative approach or different solution

// ================================================================
// DESIGN PRINCIPLES
// ================================================================

// 1. STRICT WHERE IT MATTERS (graph integrity):
//    - Link.concept: ref Artifact + (must resolve)
//    - Link.relation: ref Artifact + (must resolve)
//
// 2. FLEXIBLE WHERE IT HELPS (classification):
//    - category: word (any value, no validation)
//    - topic_type: word (any value, no validation)
//
// 3. GRANULARITY FOR AI:
//    - Target 10-30 lines per artifact
//    - Single clear purpose
//    - Precise context retrieval
//
// 4. OPTIONAL METADATA:
//    - Only create category/type Artifacts when they add value
//    - Don't create Artifacts that just repeat their name
//    - Metadata is for filtering and organization, not constraints
